IBM Plex Serif Thin Regular (IBMPlexSerif-Thin.ttf)

name

Mac NID 6

Mac NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'IBMPlexSerif-Thin', Everything looks good.

IBM Plex Serif Thin Regular (IBMPlexSerif-Thin.ttf)

name

Mac NID 16/17

Mac NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'IBM Plex Serif' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Thin' = NID 1 'IBM Plex Serif Thin'.

IBM Plex Serif Thin Regular (IBMPlexSerif-Thin.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'IBMPlexSerif-Thin', Everything looks good.

IBM Plex Serif Thin Regular (IBMPlexSerif-Thin.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'IBM Plex Serif' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Thin' = NID 1 'IBM Plex Serif Thin'.

IBM Plex Serif Thin Italic (IBMPlexSerif-ThinItalic.ttf)

name

Mac NID 6

Mac NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'IBMPlexSerif-ThinItalic', Everything looks good.

Pass

IBM Plex Serif Thin Italic (IBMPlexSerif-ThinItalic.ttf)

name

Mac NID 16/17

Mac NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'IBM Plex Serif' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Thin Italic' = NID 1 'IBM Plex Serif Thin' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Pass

This font software is the property of Monotype Imaging Inc., or one of its affiliated entities (collectively, Monotype) and its use by you is covered under the terms of a license agreement. You have obtained this font software either directly from Monotype or together with software distributed by one of the licensees of Monotype. This software is a valuable asset of Monotype. Unless you have entered into a specific license agreement granting you additional rights, your use of this software is limited by the terms of the actual license agreement you have entered into with Monotype. You may not copy or distribute this software. If you have any questions concerning your rights you should review the license agreement you received with the software. IBM Plex Serif Thin Italic (IBMPlexSerif-ThinItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'IBM Plex Serif' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Thin Italic' = NID 1 'IBM Plex Serif Thin' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Pass

IBM Plex Serif ExtraLight Italic (IBMPlexSerif-ExtraLightItalic.ttf)

name

Mac NID 6

Mac NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'IBMPlexSerif-ExtraLightItalic', Everything looks good.

IBM Plex Serif ExtraLight Italic (IBMPlexSerif-ExtraLightItalic.ttf)

name

Mac NID 16/17

Mac NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'IBM Plex Serif' + 'Space' + NID 17 'ExtraLight Italic' = NID 1 'IBM Plex Serif ExtraLight' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Pass

IBM Plex Serif ExtraLight Italic (IBMPlexSerif-ExtraLightItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'IBMPlexSerif-ExtraLightItalic', Everything looks good.

IBM Plex Serif ExtraLight Italic (IBMPlexSerif-ExtraLightItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'IBM Plex Serif' + 'Space' + NID 17 'ExtraLight Italic' = NID 1 'IBM Plex Serif ExtraLight' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

You have obtained this font software either directly from Monotype or together with software distributed by one of the licensees of Monotype. This software is a valuable asset of Monotype. Unless you have entered into a specific license agreement granting you additional rights, your use of this software is limited by the terms of the actual license agreement you have entered into with Monotype. You may not copy or distribute this software. If you have any questions concerning your rights you should review the license agreement you received with the software. You can learn more about Monotype by clicking here: www.monotype.com.

IBM Plex Serif Light Italic (IBMPlexSerif-LightItalic.ttf)

name

Mac NID 16/17

Mac NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'IBM Plex Serif' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Light Italic' = NID 1 'IBM Plex Serif Light' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Pass

IBM Plex Serif Light Italic (IBMPlexSerif-LightItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'IBMPlexSerif-LightItalic', Everything looks good.

Pass

Mac NID 6

NID 6 is 'IBMPlexSerif-Italic', Everything looks good.

IBM Plex Serif Medium Regular (IBMPlexSerif-Medium.ttf)

name

Mac NID 6

Mac NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'IBMPlexSerif-Medium', Everything looks good.

IBM Plex Serif Medium Regular (IBMPlexSerif-Medium.ttf)

name

Mac NID 16/17

Mac NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'IBM Plex Serif' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Medium' = NID 1 'IBM Plex Serif Medium'.

Pass

IBM Plex Serif Medium Italic (IBMPlexSerif-MediumItalic.ttf)

name

Mac NID 16/17

Mac NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'IBM Plex Serif' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Medium Italic' = NID 1 'IBM Plex Serif Medium' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Pass

IBM Plex Serif Medium Italic (IBMPlexSerif-MediumItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'IBMPlexSerif-MediumItalic', Everything looks good.

Pass

IBM Plex Serif Medium Italic (IBMPlexSerif-MediumItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'IBM Plex Serif' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Medium Italic' = NID 1 'IBM Plex Serif Medium' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Pass

IBM Plex Serif SemiBold Regular (IBMPlexSerif-SemiBold.ttf)

name

Mac NID 6

Mac NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'IBMPlexSerif-SemiBold', Everything looks good.

IBM Plex Serif SemiBold Regular (IBMPlexSerif-SemiBold.ttf)

name

Mac NID 16/17

Mac NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'IBM Plex Serif' + 'Space' + NID 17 'SemiBold' = NID 1 'IBM Plex Serif SemiBold'.

Pass

Unless you have entered into a specific license agreement granting you additional rights, your use of this software is limited by the terms of the actual license agreement you have entered into with Monotype. IBM Plex Serif SemiBold Regular (IBMPlexSerif-SemiBold.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'IBM Plex Serif' + 'Space' + NID 17 'SemiBold' = NID 1 'IBM Plex Serif SemiBold'.

Pass

IBM Plex Serif Bold (IBMPlexSerif-Bold.ttf)

name

Mac NID 6

Mac NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'IBMPlexSerif-Bold', Everything looks good.

Pass

IBM Plex Serif Bold Italic (IBMPlexSerif-BoldItalic.ttf)

name

Mac NID 6

Mac NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.

, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'IBMPlexSerif-BoldItalic', Everything looks good.

MS [3, 1, 1033] is: 'How razorback-jumping frogs can level six piqued gymnasts!'

gasp

Default

Pull gasp table Default.

Grid-fit = True, Do gray = True, Symmetric grid-fit = True, Symmetric smoothing = True

Pass

IBM Plex Serif Thin Regular (IBMPlexSerif-Thin.ttf)

gasp

Default

Check gasp table Default.

gasp table default is:
Grid-fit = True, Do gray = True, Symmetric grid-fit = True, Symmetric smoothing = True
and should be:
Grid-fit = True, Do gray = True, Symmetric grid-fit = True, Symmetric smoothing = True

Info

subtable

Pull gasp subtable: '8'

Do gray = True, Symmetric smoothing = True

head

lowestRecPPEM

Monotype standard for lowestRecPPEM is '9'.

lowestRecPPEM is '9', but should be '9'

Pass

gasp

subtable

gasp subtable value should be one less than lowestRecPPEM (head table).

gasp subtable is '8' and should be '8'.
(head table lowestRecPPEM is '9')

Pass

subtable

'Do gray = True, Symmetric smoothing = True'
equal to MT standard
'Do gray = True, Symmetric smoothing = True'

Pass

IBM Plex Serif Bold Italic (IBMPlexSerif-BoldItalic.ttf)

gasp

Default

Check gasp table Default.

gasp table default is:
Grid-fit = True, Do gray = True, Symmetric grid-fit = True, Symmetric smoothing = True
and should be:
Grid-fit = True, Do gray = True, Symmetric grid-fit = True, Symmetric smoothing = True

Info

IBM Plex Serif Bold Italic (IBMPlexSerif-BoldItalic.ttf)

gasp

subtable

Do gray = True, Symmetric smoothing = True

Pass

IBM Plex Serif Bold Italic (IBMPlexSerif-BoldItalic.ttf)

head

lowestRecPPEM

Monotype standard for lowestRecPPEM is '9'.

lowestRecPPEM is '9', but should be '9'

Pass

subtable

gasp subtable is '8' and should be '8'.
(head table lowestRecPPEM is '9')
